<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="310" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,188,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,188,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[285,445,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atomosphyrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[285,445,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Atomosphyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[582,683,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Thiodina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[582,683,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Thiodina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[702,826,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cyllodania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[702,826,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Cyllodania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[846,948,189,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hyetussa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[846,948,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Hyetussa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1917" box="[968,1124,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Arachnomura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[968,1124,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Arachnomura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1188,1307,189,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Tartamura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1188,1307,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Tartamura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having spine-like setae on the anterior surface of male chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[839,929,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[170,1434,180,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[170,1434,180,1741]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Atomosphyrus tristiculus, male. A face; B detail of chelicerae, anterior view; C left chelicera, lateral view; D anterior scales of abdomen, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098050/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
) (hard to see in black species, such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atomosphyrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristiculus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">At. tristiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without an adequate light and contrast, or without SEM). The genus differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[1248,1351,261,284]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hyetussa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1248,1351,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Hyetussa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the filiform embolus curling around the bulb (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano" box="[684,842,295,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1966) Salticidae (Araneae) formiciformes VI. El genero Atomosphyrus Simon, 1902. Physis, Buenos Aires (C), 26, 279 - 284." type="journal article" year="1966">Galiano 1966</bibRefCitation>
: figs 5‒6, 15‒16); from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[1124,1225,295,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Thiodina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1124,1225,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Thiodina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of dorsal abdominal pattern (
<figureCitation box="[464,611,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,193,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[183,1407,193,1484]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Atomosphyrus tristiculus and its model Camponotus cf. chilensis (Formicidae: Formicinae). A‒D At. tristiculus live specimens (A‒B male, C‒D female); E‒F Camponotus cf. chilensis live specimens. Photo credits: A‒B, E‒F Bernardo Segura; C‒D Christian Lukhaup." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098042/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Figs 1A‒1D</figureCitation>
) (abdomen entirely black in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[967,1127,332,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atomosphyrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[967,1127,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Atomosphyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1917" box="[1226,1382,332,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Arachnomura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1226,1382,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Arachnomura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,270,369,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Tartamura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,270,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Tartamura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a keel on the anterior face of male chelicera; and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[1007,1132,367,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cyllodania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1007,1132,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Cyllodania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by this keel being strongly modified into a “mastidion” in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[515,675,404,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atomosphyrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[515,675,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Atomosphyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the proximal portion of male chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1331,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[170,1434,180,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[170,1434,180,1741]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Atomosphyrus tristiculus, male. A face; B detail of chelicerae, anterior view; C left chelicera, lateral view; D anterior scales of abdomen, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098050/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Figs 5A‒5C</figureCitation>
; also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano" box="[151,306,439,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1966) Salticidae (Araneae) formiciformes VI. El genero Atomosphyrus Simon, 1902. Physis, Buenos Aires (C), 26, 279 - 284." type="journal article" year="1966">Galiano 1966</bibRefCitation>
: figs 10, 12), and by the filiform embolus.
</paragraph>
